  <h3 class="ui header">
    <i class="settings icon"></i>
    Configuring your Okta org
  </h3>
  <p>
    If you don't
    <a href="https://www.okta.com/developer/signup/">
      have an Okta org
    </a>
    or haven't
    <a href="https://help.okta.com/en/prev/Content/Topics/Apps/Apps_App_Integration_Wizard.htm?Highlight=openid%20connect#OIDCWizard">
      set up an OIDC app
    </a>
    yet,
    you can use the included mock Okta server for quick testing:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="bash"># Start the mock-okta server on http://127.0.0.1:{{config.mockOkta.port}}
[samples]$ npm run mock-okta

  </code></pre>

  <p>
    To test these samples against your own Okta org and OIDC app, update
    the following settings in <strong>.samples.config.json</strong> and restart
    your server:
  </p>
  <table class="ui table compact collapsing">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Setting</th>
        <th>Value</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>oidc.oktaUrl</td>
        <td>The base url for your okta org, i.e. https://your-org.okta.com</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>oidc.clientId</td>
        <td>
          The clientId for your OIDC app.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>oidc.clientSecret</td>
        <td>The clientSecret for your OIDC app</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

