      <p>
        This is a generated sample app built in Vanilla Javascript - it contains
        the markup and logic you'll need to build your own sample.
      </p>
      <strong>What you need to do:</strong>
      <div class="ui list">
        <div class="item">
          <i class="code icon"></i>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="header">
              Replace the vanilla JS files in the app/ directory with code for
              your frontend framework.
            </div>
            <div class="description">
              <div class="ui bulleted list">
                <div class="item">
                  The sample renders to the right hand column - you should not
                  need to modify the doc templates.
                </div>
                <div class="item">
                  See the
                  <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/okta/samples-js-angular-1/tree/master/app">
                    Angular 1 Sample
                  </a>
                  for an example of how to do this.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <i class="terminal icon"></i>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="header">
              Run "npm test" to verify that you've implemented the views correctly.
            </div>
            <div class="description">
              This is a set of end-to-end selenium tests that cover the scenarios
              we care about.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
          <i class="hand peace icon"></i>
          <div class="content">
            <div class="header">
              Once you've passed the tests, you're done! Well, almost.
            </div>
            <div class="description">
              Follow the guidelines to
              <a target="_blank" href="https://github.com/okta/generator-samples#publishing-your-samples">
                publish your sample
              </a>.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
